{
  "$schema": "https://json.schemastore.org/sarif-2.1.0.json",
  "version": "2.1.0",
  "runs": [
    {
      "tool": {
        "driver": {
          "name": "AgentAuditKit",
          "version": "0.2.0",
          "semanticVersion": "0.2.0",
          "informationUri": "https://github.com/sattyamjjain/agent-audit-kit",
          "rules": [
            {
              "id": "AAK-MCP-003",
              "name": "McpEnvExposesSecrets",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "MCP server environment exposes secrets"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Hardcoded secrets found in mcpServers env block. Secrets in project-scoped MCP config are committed to git."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://owasp.org/www-project-mcp-top-10/",
              "help": {
                "text": "Use environment variable references or a secrets manager.\n\nReferences:\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP01:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI03\n- Adversa: ADV-TOKEN-01",
                "markdown": "**Remediation:** Use environment variable references or a secrets manager.\n\n**References:**\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP01:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI03\n- Adversa: ADV-TOKEN-01"
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "properties": {
                "security-severity": "7.5",
                "precision": "high",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "mcp-config",
                  "OWASP-Agentic-ASI03",
                  "Adversa-ADV-TOKEN-01"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "AAK-MCP-006",
              "name": "McpCommandRelativePath",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "MCP server command uses relative path"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "The command uses a relative path that can be hijacked via PATH manipulation."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://owasp.org/www-project-mcp-top-10/",
              "help": {
                "text": "Use absolute paths for MCP server executables.\n\nReferences:\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP04:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI05\n- Adversa: ADV-INJECT-02",
                "markdown": "**Remediation:** Use absolute paths for MCP server executables.\n\n**References:**\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP04:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI05\n- Adversa: ADV-INJECT-02"
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "properties": {
                "security-severity": "5.0",
                "precision": "high",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "mcp-config",
                  "OWASP-Agentic-ASI05",
                  "Adversa-ADV-INJECT-02"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "AAK-MCP-001",
              "name": "RemoteMcpServerNoAuth",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Remote MCP server without authentication"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "An MCP server uses HTTP transport (url field) without any authentication headers. Unauthenticated remote servers can be MITM'd or spoofed."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://owasp.org/www-project-mcp-top-10/",
              "help": {
                "text": "Add OAuth 2.1 bearer token or API key header authentication.\n\nReferences:\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP07:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI03\n- Adversa: ADV-AUTH-01",
                "markdown": "**Remediation:** Add OAuth 2.1 bearer token or API key header authentication.\n\n**References:**\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP07:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI03\n- Adversa: ADV-AUTH-01"
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "properties": {
                "security-severity": "9.5",
                "precision": "high",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "mcp-config",
                  "OWASP-Agentic-ASI03",
                  "Adversa-ADV-AUTH-01"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "AAK-MCP-005",
              "name": "McpRuntimePackageFetch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "MCP server uses npx/uvx to fetch and execute remote packages"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "The command uses npx, uvx, bunx, or pnpx which fetches the latest version from a registry at runtime, vulnerable to typosquatting and dependency confusion."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://owasp.org/www-project-mcp-top-10/",
              "help": {
                "text": "Pin exact package versions or use locally installed packages.\n\nReferences:\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP03:2025\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP10:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI04\n- Adversa: ADV-SUPPLY-01",
                "markdown": "**Remediation:** Pin exact package versions or use locally installed packages.\n\n**References:**\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP03:2025\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP10:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI04\n- Adversa: ADV-SUPPLY-01"
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "properties": {
                "security-severity": "5.0",
                "precision": "high",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "mcp-config",
                  "OWASP-Agentic-ASI04",
                  "Adversa-ADV-SUPPLY-01"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "AAK-MCP-007",
              "name": "McpUnpinnedPackageVersion",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "MCP server lacks version pinning in args"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Package name in args lacks @version suffix when using npx/uvx. Unpinned packages can silently update to malicious versions."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://owasp.org/www-project-mcp-top-10/",
              "help": {
                "text": "Pin with @x.y.z suffix, e.g., @modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem@2025.1.1\n\nReferences:\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP03:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI04\n- Adversa: ADV-SUPPLY-02",
                "markdown": "**Remediation:** Pin with @x.y.z suffix, e.g., @modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem@2025.1.1\n\n**References:**\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP03:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI04\n- Adversa: ADV-SUPPLY-02"
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "properties": {
                "security-severity": "2.0",
                "precision": "high",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "mcp-config",
                  "OWASP-Agentic-ASI04",
                  "Adversa-ADV-SUPPLY-02"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "AAK-MCP-008",
              "name": "McpHeadersHelperShellExec",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "MCP server headersHelper executes arbitrary commands"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "The headersHelper field executes arbitrary shell commands to generate headers. A malicious repo can exfiltrate data via header generation."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://owasp.org/www-project-mcp-top-10/",
              "help": {
                "text": "Avoid headersHelper in project-scoped configs. Use static headers or OAuth flows instead.\n\nReferences:\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP04:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI05\n- Adversa: ADV-INJECT-03",
                "markdown": "**Remediation:** Avoid headersHelper in project-scoped configs. Use static headers or OAuth flows instead.\n\n**References:**\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP04:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI05\n- Adversa: ADV-INJECT-03"
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "properties": {
                "security-severity": "9.5",
                "precision": "high",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "mcp-config",
                  "OWASP-Agentic-ASI05",
                  "Adversa-ADV-INJECT-03"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "AAK-MCP-010",
              "name": "McpFilesystemRootAccess",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "MCP server config allows arbitrary filesystem root access"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "An MCP server is configured with filesystem root (/) or home directory access, allowing unrestricted file operations."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://owasp.org/www-project-mcp-top-10/",
              "help": {
                "text": "Restrict filesystem access to specific project directories only.\n\nReferences:\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP06:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI02\n- Adversa: ADV-SCOPE-02",
                "markdown": "**Remediation:** Restrict filesystem access to specific project directories only.\n\n**References:**\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP06:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI02\n- Adversa: ADV-SCOPE-02"
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "properties": {
                "security-severity": "7.5",
                "precision": "high",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "mcp-config",
                  "OWASP-Agentic-ASI02",
                  "Adversa-ADV-SCOPE-02"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "AAK-HOOK-007",
              "name": "ExcessiveHookCount",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Excessive number of hooks defined"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "More than 15 hook definitions in a single settings file. Large hook surface increases audit burden and risk of hidden malicious hooks."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://owasp.org/www-project-mcp-top-10/",
              "help": {
                "text": "Minimize hooks to essential operations only.\n\nReferences:\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP02:2025\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP08:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI02\n- Adversa: ADV-SCOPE-03",
                "markdown": "**Remediation:** Minimize hooks to essential operations only.\n\n**References:**\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP02:2025\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP08:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI02\n- Adversa: ADV-SCOPE-03"
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "properties": {
                "security-severity": "5.0",
                "precision": "high",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "hook-injection",
                  "OWASP-Agentic-ASI02",
                  "Adversa-ADV-SCOPE-03"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "AAK-SECRET-001",
              "name": "AnthropicApiKeyExposed",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Anthropic API key exposed"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "An Anthropic API key (sk-ant-*) was found in a project file. This allows full API access and billing abuse."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://owasp.org/www-project-mcp-top-10/",
              "help": {
                "text": "Remove key, rotate immediately, use environment variables.\n\nReferences:\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP01:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI03\n- Adversa: ADV-TOKEN-03",
                "markdown": "**Remediation:** Remove key, rotate immediately, use environment variables.\n\n**References:**\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP01:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI03\n- Adversa: ADV-TOKEN-03"
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "properties": {
                "security-severity": "9.5",
                "precision": "high",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "secret-exposure",
                  "OWASP-Agentic-ASI03",
                  "Adversa-ADV-TOKEN-03"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "AAK-SECRET-002",
              "name": "OpenaiApiKeyExposed",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "OpenAI API key exposed"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "An OpenAI API key (sk-*) was found in a project file."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://owasp.org/www-project-mcp-top-10/",
              "help": {
                "text": "Remove key, rotate immediately, use environment variables.\n\nReferences:\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP01:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI03\n- Adversa: ADV-TOKEN-04",
                "markdown": "**Remediation:** Remove key, rotate immediately, use environment variables.\n\n**References:**\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP01:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI03\n- Adversa: ADV-TOKEN-04"
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "properties": {
                "security-severity": "9.5",
                "precision": "high",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "secret-exposure",
                  "OWASP-Agentic-ASI03",
                  "Adversa-ADV-TOKEN-04"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "AAK-SECRET-003",
              "name": "AwsCredentialsExposed",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "AWS credentials exposed"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "AWS access key ID or secret access key found in a project file."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://owasp.org/www-project-mcp-top-10/",
              "help": {
                "text": "Use IAM roles, AWS SSO, or secrets manager.\n\nReferences:\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP01:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI03\n- Adversa: ADV-TOKEN-05",
                "markdown": "**Remediation:** Use IAM roles, AWS SSO, or secrets manager.\n\n**References:**\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP01:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI03\n- Adversa: ADV-TOKEN-05"
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "properties": {
                "security-severity": "9.5",
                "precision": "high",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "secret-exposure",
                  "OWASP-Agentic-ASI03",
                  "Adversa-ADV-TOKEN-05"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "AAK-SECRET-008",
              "name": "GitTokenExposed",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "GitHub/GitLab personal access token exposed"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A GitHub or GitLab personal access token (ghp_*, glpat-*) was found in a project file."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://owasp.org/www-project-mcp-top-10/",
              "help": {
                "text": "Remove token, rotate immediately, use environment variables.\n\nReferences:\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP01:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI03\n- Adversa: ADV-TOKEN-10",
                "markdown": "**Remediation:** Remove token, rotate immediately, use environment variables.\n\n**References:**\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP01:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI03\n- Adversa: ADV-TOKEN-10"
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "properties": {
                "security-severity": "9.5",
                "precision": "high",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "secret-exposure",
                  "OWASP-Agentic-ASI03",
                  "Adversa-ADV-TOKEN-10"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "AAK-SECRET-004",
              "name": "GenericHighEntropySecret",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Generic high-entropy secret"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A value assigned to a secret-like key has high Shannon entropy, indicating a likely credential or API key."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://owasp.org/www-project-mcp-top-10/",
              "help": {
                "text": "Move to environment variables or secrets manager.\n\nReferences:\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP01:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI03\n- Adversa: ADV-TOKEN-06",
                "markdown": "**Remediation:** Move to environment variables or secrets manager.\n\n**References:**\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP01:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI03\n- Adversa: ADV-TOKEN-06"
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "properties": {
                "security-severity": "7.5",
                "precision": "high",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "secret-exposure",
                  "OWASP-Agentic-ASI03",
                  "Adversa-ADV-TOKEN-06"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "AAK-SECRET-007",
              "name": "SecretInMcpEnvBlock",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Secret in MCP server environment block"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Hardcoded secret values found in mcpServers env blocks in non-.mcp.json files."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://owasp.org/www-project-mcp-top-10/",
              "help": {
                "text": "Use environment variable references.\n\nReferences:\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP01:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI03\n- Adversa: ADV-TOKEN-09",
                "markdown": "**Remediation:** Use environment variable references.\n\n**References:**\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP01:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI03\n- Adversa: ADV-TOKEN-09"
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "properties": {
                "security-severity": "5.0",
                "precision": "high",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "secret-exposure",
                  "OWASP-Agentic-ASI03",
                  "Adversa-ADV-TOKEN-09"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "AAK-POISON-001",
              "name": "ToolDescInvisibleUnicode",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Invisible Unicode characters in tool description"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Tool description contains invisible Unicode characters (zero-width joiners, RTL overrides, invisible separators) that could hide malicious instructions."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://owasp.org/www-project-mcp-top-10/",
              "help": {
                "text": "Remove invisible characters from tool descriptions.\n\nReferences:\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP05:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI06\n- Adversa: ADV-POISON-01",
                "markdown": "**Remediation:** Remove invisible characters from tool descriptions.\n\n**References:**\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP05:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI06\n- Adversa: ADV-POISON-01"
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "properties": {
                "security-severity": "9.5",
                "precision": "high",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "tool-poisoning",
                  "OWASP-Agentic-ASI06",
                  "Adversa-ADV-POISON-01"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "AAK-POISON-002",
              "name": "ToolDescPromptInjection",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Prompt injection patterns in tool description"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Tool description contains prompt injection patterns such as 'ignore previous instructions', 'system:', or role-switching directives."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://owasp.org/www-project-mcp-top-10/",
              "help": {
                "text": "Remove injection patterns from tool descriptions.\n\nReferences:\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP05:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI06\n- Adversa: ADV-POISON-02",
                "markdown": "**Remediation:** Remove injection patterns from tool descriptions.\n\n**References:**\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP05:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI06\n- Adversa: ADV-POISON-02"
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "properties": {
                "security-severity": "9.5",
                "precision": "high",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "tool-poisoning",
                  "OWASP-Agentic-ASI06",
                  "Adversa-ADV-POISON-02"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "AAK-POISON-006",
              "name": "ToolDescUrlOrPath",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "URL or file path in tool description"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Tool description contains URLs or file paths that could direct the agent to access external resources."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://owasp.org/www-project-mcp-top-10/",
              "help": {
                "text": "Remove URLs and file paths from tool descriptions.\n\nReferences:\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP05:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI06\n- Adversa: ADV-POISON-06",
                "markdown": "**Remediation:** Remove URLs and file paths from tool descriptions.\n\n**References:**\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP05:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI06\n- Adversa: ADV-POISON-06"
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "properties": {
                "security-severity": "5.0",
                "precision": "high",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "tool-poisoning",
                  "OWASP-Agentic-ASI06",
                  "Adversa-ADV-POISON-06"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "AAK-POISON-003",
              "name": "ToolDescCrossToolRef",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Cross-tool reference in tool description"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Tool description references other tools by name, potentially triggering chain calls (e.g., 'before using this tool, first call X')."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://owasp.org/www-project-mcp-top-10/",
              "help": {
                "text": "Tool descriptions should be self-contained and not reference other tools.\n\nReferences:\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP05:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI06\n- Adversa: ADV-POISON-03",
                "markdown": "**Remediation:** Tool descriptions should be self-contained and not reference other tools.\n\n**References:**\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP05:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI06\n- Adversa: ADV-POISON-03"
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "properties": {
                "security-severity": "7.5",
                "precision": "high",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "tool-poisoning",
                  "OWASP-Agentic-ASI06",
                  "Adversa-ADV-POISON-03"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "AAK-TRANSPORT-001",
              "name": "McpHttpNotHttps",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "MCP server uses HTTP instead of HTTPS"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "An MCP server URL uses HTTP instead of HTTPS, exposing all traffic including credentials to interception."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://owasp.org/www-project-mcp-top-10/",
              "help": {
                "text": "Use HTTPS for all remote MCP server connections.\n\nReferences:\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP07:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI03\n- Adversa: ADV-TRANSPORT-01",
                "markdown": "**Remediation:** Use HTTPS for all remote MCP server connections.\n\n**References:**\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP07:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI03\n- Adversa: ADV-TRANSPORT-01"
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "properties": {
                "security-severity": "9.5",
                "precision": "high",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "transport-security",
                  "OWASP-Agentic-ASI03",
                  "Adversa-ADV-TRANSPORT-01"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "AAK-TRANSPORT-003",
              "name": "McpDeprecatedSse",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Deprecated SSE transport in use"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "An MCP server uses deprecated Server-Sent Events (SSE) transport instead of Streamable HTTP."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://owasp.org/www-project-mcp-top-10/",
              "help": {
                "text": "Migrate to Streamable HTTP transport (MCP spec 2025-03-26+).\n\nReferences:\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP07:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI08\n- Adversa: ADV-TRANSPORT-03",
                "markdown": "**Remediation:** Migrate to Streamable HTTP transport (MCP spec 2025-03-26+).\n\n**References:**\n- OWASP MCP Top 10: MCP07:2025\n- OWASP Agentic: ASI08\n- Adversa: ADV-TRANSPORT-03"
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "properties": {
                "security-severity": "5.0",
                "precision": "high",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "transport-security",
                  "OWASP-Agentic-ASI08",
                  "Adversa-ADV-TRANSPORT-03"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "automationDetails": {
        "id": "agent-audit-kit/"
      },
      "results": [
        {
          "ruleId": "AAK-MCP-003",
          "ruleIndex": 0,
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "Hardcoded secrets found in mcpServers env block. Secrets in project-scoped MCP config are committed to git.\n\nEvidence: Server 'command-injection-lab' env.OPENAI_API_KEY = (hardcoded value)"
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "dvmcp-inspired.mcp.json",
